Ifeanyi Onuba, Abuja The Federal Government on Wednesday assured of the production, transportation and distribution of essential products such as food, medical, pharmaceutical and agro-allied products. It said the distribution would continue unhindered throughout the period of the coronavirus pandemic in the country. The Minister of Industry, Trade and Investment, Adeniyi Adebayo, disclosed that the Federal Government was working assiduously to mitigate the effects of COVID-19 lockdown on the economy. Adebayo stated these in Abuja during his weekly update on the performance of the Emergency Operation Centre of the Committee on Sustainable Production and Delivery of Essential Commodities During COVID-19 in Abuja. Copyright PUNCH.
